cs.DC, cs.NA, cs.AR, cs.MS, cs.SC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a scalable implementation of sparse matrix-vector multiplication on GPGPU clusters. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper deals with performance properties of spMVM with matrices of various sparsity patterns. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is another possible category as the paper focuses on the nVidia "Fermi" class of GPGPUs. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new storage format for sparse matrices. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with mathematical computations involving sparse matrices.
